{"content": "Let's double-check the calculation step by step.\n\nGiven:\n\\[\na_n = (-1)^{n+1} (3n + 2)\n\\]\n\nLet's write a few terms to spot the pattern:\n\n- \\( a_1 = (+1) \\cdot (3 \\cdot 1 + 2) = 5 \\)\n- \\( a_2 = (-1) \\cdot (3 \\cdot 2 + 2) = -8 \\)\n- \\( a_3 = (+1) \\cdot (3 \\cdot 3 + 2) = 11 \\)\n- \\( a_4 = (-1) \\cdot (3 \\cdot 4 + 2) = -14 \\)\n- \\( a_5 = (+1) \\cdot (3 \\cdot 5 + 2) = 17 \\)\n- \\( a_6 = (-1) \\cdot (3 \\cdot 6 + 2) = -20 \\)\n\nNow, let's group the terms in pairs:\n\\[\n(a_1 + a_2), (a_3 + a_4), \\dots, (a_{99} + a_{100})\n\\]\n\nCompute one pair:\n\\[\na_{2k-1} + a_{2k}\n\\]\n\\[\n= (-1)^{2k-1+1}(3(2k-1) + 2) + (-1)^{2k+1}(3(2k) + 2)\n\\]\n\\[\n= (-1)^{2k}(3(2k-1) + 2) + (-1)^{2k+1}(3(2k) + 2)\n\\]\n\\[\n= 1 \\cdot (3(2k-1) + 2) + (-1) \\cdot (3(2k) + 2)\n", "in": 420, "out": 400}